    <name>Support a Growth Mindset by Teaching Adults About Neuroplasticity </name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{b45f7269-c7cc-4bbe-bad0-96b5a042806c}{147}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Adult learners must see the benefit of learning tasks to fully engage. Adults are independent&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;and&amp;nbsp;have complex reasons for setting goals. Help them see the benefits of learning math and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;developing a growth mindset by teaching them about neuroplasticity—or the ability of the brain&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;to respond to the environment and form new connections.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{b45f7269-c7cc-4bbe-bad0-96b5a042806c}{150}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Even as adults, human brains are engaging in learning and growing. Deliberate practice improves&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;memory. However, practice must be engaging.&amp;nbsp;This is why&amp;nbsp;adults,&amp;nbsp;especially, need&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;multiple ways&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;to learn the same new concept or skill&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; Frequent feedback activates learning and strengthens&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;connections. Neuroplasticity is a significant component of Universal Design for Learning&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9757@$" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(CAST,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;n.d.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{b45f7269-c7cc-4bbe-bad0-96b5a042806c}{150}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a data-sessionid="5453353d-90ec-4c5b-8798-affc98e71156" data-shapeids="5" data-slide=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Additional%20Resources%20%281%29.png" alt="" width="68" height="66" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Additional Resource:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?embed=no&amp;amp;v=LNHBMFCzznE" target="_blank"&gt;After watching this, your brain will not be the same&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;, Lara Boyd&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;discusses neuroplasticity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;
